18:20.580 --> 18:23.980
Our show today continues the discussion with Philip Jose Farmer.

18:24.280 --> 18:27.920
A major incident in Farmer's career began when Venus on the Half-Shell,

18:28.160 --> 18:30.400
a novel written under the pseudonym Kilgore Trout,

18:30.600 --> 18:34.900
appeared in the pages of fantasy and science fiction in late 74, early 75.

18:35.320 --> 18:38.600
Of course, Kilgore Trout is the creation of author Kurt Vonnegut, Jr.

18:39.020 --> 18:42.680
The character Trout is an impoverished, underappreciated science fiction writer

18:42.680 --> 18:44.840
who appears in a number of Vonnegut's novels.

18:45.120 --> 18:47.840
We asked Farmer if he identifies with Kilgore Trout.

18:48.860 --> 18:50.780
I was a fan of Vonnegut's novels.

18:51.040 --> 18:54.440
I liked all his books, but Kilgore Trout really turned me on

18:54.440 --> 18:59.500
because his early experiences, and as a matter of fact his later ones too,

19:00.200 --> 19:02.720
were like a lot of my early experiences,

19:02.840 --> 19:08.020
and a lot like the experiences of many other science fiction writers.

19:08.280 --> 19:11.200
Back in the old days when they weren't being paid much,

19:11.200 --> 19:13.700
and science fiction was looked down upon,

19:14.600 --> 19:20.380
and we were being taken due to our inexperience by various publishers and agents.

19:22.140 --> 19:24.900
Also, I had a tough time getting any recognition.

19:26.200 --> 19:29.000
So, I guess that's why I identified with him,

19:29.280 --> 19:30.760
plus the fact he's a great character.

19:32.260 --> 19:35.820
Vonnegut did not appreciate the reviews given Venus on the Half-Shell,

19:36.100 --> 19:37.140
either pro or con,

19:37.140 --> 19:40.860
because most of the reviewers approached the work as if Vonnegut were the author.

19:41.140 --> 19:45.700
This caused Farmer the opportunity to write another novel under the Kilgore Trout pseudonym.

19:46.820 --> 19:49.920
I don't know what his reactions are to the novel itself,

19:50.020 --> 19:54.880
but so many people thought that he'd written it,

19:55.040 --> 19:57.540
and he would tell you it's hundreds of maybe thousands,

19:57.880 --> 20:00.820
but then the reviews came out.

20:01.460 --> 20:04.200
Some said Venus on the Half Shell by Kilgore Trout.

20:05.960 --> 20:07.560
It was the worst thing he'd written,

20:07.640 --> 20:09.620
and others said it was the best thing he'd ever written.

20:11.520 --> 20:14.780
When I applied for permission to write The Son of Jimmy Valentine,

20:14.980 --> 20:17.080
which I really would have loved to have done,

20:17.240 --> 20:18.720
because I could have had a lot of fun with it,

20:20.060 --> 20:20.920
he said no,

20:21.880 --> 20:23.360
which is his prerogative.

20:24.580 --> 20:29.160
We asked if The Son of Jimmy Valentine was Kilgore Trout's one erotic novel.

20:30.340 --> 20:31.840
It was his, uh,

20:32.300 --> 20:35.820
not only his one and only specifically erotic book,

20:35.860 --> 20:38.780
it was also his only non-science fiction book.

20:39.740 --> 20:42.720
Farmer obviously enjoys writing about fictional authors,

20:42.780 --> 20:45.040
who in turn write about their own fictional authors,

20:45.120 --> 20:45.900
and so on.

20:46.080 --> 20:49.240
Listen as he describes what writing as Kilgore Trout started.

20:50.240 --> 20:52.000
In the Venus on the Half-Shell,

20:52.680 --> 20:52.720
uh,

20:54.160 --> 20:54.820
the protagonist,

20:55.200 --> 20:56.180
Simon Wagstaff,

20:56.260 --> 20:58.780
had his favorite science fiction author.

20:59.720 --> 21:01.460
Just as in the Vonnegut books,

21:02.200 --> 21:04.100
Eliot Rosewater thought that

21:05.020 --> 21:06.860
Kilgore Trout was the greatest, uh,

21:07.020 --> 21:07.580
living writer,

21:07.680 --> 21:07.900
you know,

21:07.940 --> 21:09.300
in any field.

21:09.400 --> 21:10.700
He should have been president of the U.S.

21:10.760 --> 21:11.940
He could have solved all the problems.

21:12.460 --> 21:12.940
Well,

21:12.960 --> 21:13.240
anyway,

21:13.380 --> 21:14.520
in Venus on the Half Shell,

21:14.520 --> 21:14.960
uh,

21:16.240 --> 21:19.460
Simon Wagstaff liked to read the science fiction works of a

21:19.460 --> 21:23.080
fellow called Jonathan Swift Somers III,

21:23.520 --> 21:27.200
and I described his various works,

21:27.440 --> 21:28.040
or Al Bynum,

21:28.300 --> 21:29.340
and give the title.

21:30.240 --> 21:32.020
But Jonathan Swift Somers,

21:32.320 --> 21:33.800
who's a fiction author,

21:35.620 --> 21:39.320
wrote about a giant German shepherd police dog,

21:39.320 --> 21:43.020
whose IQ had been raised to about 200 in a laboratory,

21:43.120 --> 21:44.680
and he became a private detective.

21:45.840 --> 21:46.360
Now,

21:46.520 --> 21:46.700
uh,

21:46.840 --> 21:50.780
I plan eventually someday on writing a book by Ralph von

21:50.780 --> 21:51.400
Valvao,

21:51.600 --> 21:52.080
this dog,

21:52.300 --> 21:53.260
under the,

21:53.820 --> 21:56.200
under the name of Ralph von Valvao.

21:57.580 --> 22:00.200
And then maybe I'll end the cycle by

22:01.380 --> 22:04.400
having Ralph von Valvao write about a human named, uh,

22:04.720 --> 22:05.360
Vonnegut,

22:05.560 --> 22:06.640
or something like that,

22:07.320 --> 22:08.580
and completing it,

22:08.760 --> 22:10.140
going right back to Vonnegut again.

22:11.280 --> 22:14.140
Farmer conceived of the extended family group called the

22:14.140 --> 22:15.100
Wold-Newton family,

22:15.100 --> 22:17.780
in which many great historical and fictional characters are

22:17.780 --> 22:19.400
descended from the Scarlet Pimpernel.

22:19.740 --> 22:20.300
Thus,

22:20.380 --> 22:22.620
Kilgore Trout is related to Sherlock Holmes,

22:22.880 --> 22:23.500
Doc Savage,

22:23.780 --> 22:24.560
Sam Spade,

22:24.740 --> 22:25.540
and James Bond,

22:25.640 --> 22:26.120
among others.

22:26.360 --> 22:29.220
We will look into this aspect of Farmer's writing some more

22:29.220 --> 22:29.660
tomorrow.

